From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 14:44:38 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 08/12] drm/msm/dp: Fix parity calculation for multi-byte
 payloads

msm_dp_utils_calculate_parity() decides whether to calculate parity over
one byte or a 32-bit payload by checking only bits 8..15. Payload words
with data only in the upper two bytes are therefore treated as one-byte
values.

DSC PPS programming needs parity over packed 32-bit payload words. Check
whether any bit outside the low byte is set instead.

Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
(cherry picked from commit 77c110104f64dae36ff86ec569a3e6c1c9db6d72)
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_utils.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_utils.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_utils.c
index 4a5ebb0c33b8..945f3ef644f5 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_utils.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/dp/dp_utils.c
@@ -59,7 +59,7 @@ u8 msm_dp_utils_calculate_parity(u32 data)
 	u8 iData = 0;
 	u8 i = 0;
 	u8 parity_byte;
-	u8 num_byte = (data & 0xFF00) > 0 ? 8 : 2;
+	u8 num_byte = data > 0xFF ? 8 : 2;
 
 	for (i = 0; i < num_byte; i++) {
 		iData = (data >> i * 4) & 0xF;
